We now turn to a simulation study to demonstrate the performance of the new tests under various alternatives, specifically:
(i) elliptically symmetric SP distributions, denoted by Sα; (ii) Student t-distributions with ν degrees of freedom, denoted by tν ; (iii) skew normal distributions with skewness parameter ν, denoted by SNν ; (iv) skew Cauchy distributions with skewness parameter ν, denoted by SCν ;
The cases p = 4, 6 are considered for the dimension of the distribution. Throughout, we choose δ = 0 andQ = Ip, where Ip denotes the p× p identitymatrix. Recall in this connection that our method requires the computation of the density of a spherical SP law. Details on this computation are included in Section S4 of the online supplement.
